00:01:43.239 --> 00:01:45.900
Second Corinthians chapter number 10 this morning,

00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:48.000
and I'm thankful for God's word

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:49.800
and we've been making progress here

00:01:49.800 --> 00:01:51.559
through the book of Second Corinthians.

00:01:51.559 --> 00:01:54.519
And our theme for this year is we sang the theme song

00:01:54.559 --> 00:01:59.160
and we do to remind us that God's grace is sufficient

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:01.639
and it's our themes for this year.

00:02:01.639 --> 00:02:03.680
And I'm so thankful I preached a message

00:02:03.680 --> 00:02:06.440
from Second Corinthians 12 to begin the year.

00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:08.339
And then we've been walking through the book

00:02:08.339 --> 00:02:10.720
of Second Corinthians on Sunday mornings.

00:02:10.720 --> 00:02:14.039
And here we find ourselves in chapter number 10 this morning

00:02:14.039 --> 00:02:16.020
and we'll look at the entire chapter,

00:02:16.020 --> 00:02:17.839
Second Corinthians chapter 10 verses one

00:02:17.839 --> 00:02:19.880
through 18 this morning.

00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:21.440
And as you look at the,

00:02:21.440 --> 00:02:23.360
as we begin to look at this section

00:02:23.360 --> 00:02:24.440
of the book of Second Corinthians,

00:02:25.259 --> 00:02:27.279
there's kind of a shift in what's taking place

00:02:27.279 --> 00:02:28.539
with regard to the letter.

00:02:28.539 --> 00:02:30.919
And so let me just give a word of introduction

00:02:30.919 --> 00:02:34.399
with regard to helping us understand a little bit

00:02:34.399 --> 00:02:36.919
the platform from which Paul is writing.

00:02:36.919 --> 00:02:38.320
And we understand that all scripture

00:02:38.320 --> 00:02:40.119
is given by inspiration of God

00:02:40.119 --> 00:02:42.520
and God is using Paul to write back

00:02:42.520 --> 00:02:44.320
to this church in Corinth.

00:02:44.320 --> 00:02:46.740
And there's a group of people, false teachers,

00:02:46.740 --> 00:02:48.279
that are called the Judaizers.

00:02:48.279 --> 00:02:50.839
And these Judaizers had influenced

00:02:50.839 --> 00:02:52.880
the believers at Corinth.

00:02:52.880 --> 00:02:56.520
And this influence upon the believers at Corinth

00:02:56.520 --> 00:02:58.699
led to some of the friction.

00:02:58.699 --> 00:03:00.220
I can't say all of the friction

00:03:00.220 --> 00:03:01.720
because there were other factors as well,

00:03:01.720 --> 00:03:03.160
but led to some of the friction

00:03:03.160 --> 00:03:06.160
between the believers at the church in Corinth

00:03:06.160 --> 00:03:07.639
and the Apostle Paul.

00:03:07.639 --> 00:03:08.639
In the beginning of this book,

00:03:08.639 --> 00:03:11.619
he touched on some of those things and dealt with it.

00:03:11.619 --> 00:03:14.639
But we find that these false teachers, these Judaizers,

00:03:14.639 --> 00:03:18.039
they really had relentlessly criticized Paul

00:03:18.039 --> 00:03:19.679
and his ministry.

00:03:19.679 --> 00:03:22.720
And so throughout chapter number 10 and 11,

00:03:23.559 --> 00:03:25.960
we find that Paul will address the subject

00:03:25.960 --> 00:03:29.240
while revealing to the believers in Corinth

00:03:29.240 --> 00:03:32.080
and revealing to us by way of preservation

00:03:32.080 --> 00:03:34.800
his perspective not only on life,

00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:37.240
but his perspective on ministry.

00:03:37.240 --> 00:03:40.080
And he does not take the approach,

00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:42.320
as we'll look through the text of scripture,

00:03:42.320 --> 00:03:45.399
of doing the same thing that the Judaizers are doing.

00:03:45.399 --> 00:03:48.279
He's not gonna just get into a mud fighting contest

00:03:48.279 --> 00:03:50.279
and throw in mud at these guys.

00:03:50.279 --> 00:03:52.080
He's going to share with them

00:03:52.080 --> 00:03:54.160
the call that God's placed upon his life

00:03:54.160 --> 00:03:56.240
and his perspective on ministry

00:03:56.240 --> 00:04:00.039
and what he endeavors to accomplish with his life.

00:04:00.039 --> 00:04:01.880
You know, in verse number 18,

00:04:01.880 --> 00:04:04.119
and we'll get through the whole text this morning,

00:04:04.119 --> 00:04:06.100
but I wanna draw your attention to verse 18

00:04:06.100 --> 00:04:10.759
as we look here this morning at this text of scripture,

00:04:10.759 --> 00:04:11.600
the Bible says,

00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:16.600
for not he that commendeth himself is approved.

00:04:18.119 --> 00:04:20.519
And we know some people that commend themselves.

00:04:21.519 --> 00:04:22.920
You get into a conversation with them

00:04:22.920 --> 00:04:25.239
and they just want you to know how good they are

00:04:25.239 --> 00:04:26.820
and how wonderful they are.

00:04:26.820 --> 00:04:30.320
And they are the gift in your life.

00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:33.200
And I mean, they are just all about themselves.

00:04:33.200 --> 00:04:34.320
And here it says,

00:04:34.320 --> 00:04:38.239
for not he that commendeth himself is approved,

00:04:38.239 --> 00:04:42.519
but whom the Lord commendeth.

00:04:42.519 --> 00:04:45.239
And what a great verse of scripture

00:04:45.239 --> 00:04:49.839
for us to understand the mindset of the apostle Paul.

00:04:49.839 --> 00:04:52.920
It reminds us really of what Paul had said earlier

00:04:52.920 --> 00:04:53.799
in this book.

00:04:53.799 --> 00:04:57.100
Maybe you wanna turn back a few pages in chapter number five

00:04:57.100 --> 00:04:59.040
of second Corinthians chapter five.

00:04:59.040 --> 00:05:02.799
And remember Paul said this in verse number nine,

00:05:02.799 --> 00:05:03.640
he says,

00:05:03.640 --> 00:05:07.359
wherefore we labor that whether present or absent,

00:05:07.359 --> 00:05:10.200
we may be accepted of him.

00:05:10.200 --> 00:05:13.200
He then says this in verse number 15 of the same chapter

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:15.359
and that he died for all,

00:05:15.359 --> 00:05:17.899
speaking about the Lord Jesus Christ, God in flesh,

00:05:17.899 --> 00:05:19.799
that he died for all, why?

00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:22.799
Because all are sinners in need of a savior.

00:05:22.799 --> 00:05:25.720
They have a sin debt that can only be paid for

00:05:25.720 --> 00:05:27.200
with the blood of Christ.

00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:30.480
And so he died for all that they would live.

00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:33.399
Notice this should not henceforth live unto themselves,

00:05:33.399 --> 00:05:37.679
but unto him, which died for them and rose again.

00:05:37.679 --> 00:05:39.679
When I preached through that text of scripture

00:05:39.679 --> 00:05:41.119
in chapter number five,

00:05:41.119 --> 00:05:43.519
I actually spent several weeks in chapter number five.

00:05:43.519 --> 00:05:46.679
There's many important truths that God gives us

00:05:46.679 --> 00:05:47.720
in that chapter.

00:05:47.720 --> 00:05:50.359
And we dealt with them quite thoroughly,

00:05:50.359 --> 00:05:53.019
but we understand that the apostle Paul there

00:05:53.019 --> 00:05:54.519
in second Corinthians five,

00:05:54.519 --> 00:05:56.079
just like he's going to here

00:05:56.079 --> 00:05:58.279
in second Corinthians chapter number 10

00:05:58.279 --> 00:06:02.760
is talking about a desire for God's approval.

00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:05.059
And I've titled the message that this morning,

00:06:05.059 --> 00:06:07.799
desiring God's approval.

00:06:07.799 --> 00:06:10.720
Now understand with me in second Corinthians chapter five

00:06:10.720 --> 00:06:12.760
and also here in chapter number 10,

00:06:12.760 --> 00:06:15.660
this is not the apostle Paul talking about salvation.

00:06:15.660 --> 00:06:18.299
He was saved and he was secure

00:06:18.299 --> 00:06:21.579
because of what Christ did on the cross of Calvary.

00:06:21.579 --> 00:06:26.299
This morning, your salvation is based upon your acceptance

00:06:26.299 --> 00:06:28.820
of the free gift of eternal life

00:06:28.820 --> 00:06:32.440
that was paid for with the precious blood of Christ.

00:06:32.440 --> 00:06:34.739
There's no other name under heaven given among men

00:06:34.739 --> 00:06:38.059
whereby we must be saved.

00:06:38.059 --> 00:06:41.179
As an appointed unto man wants to die,

00:06:41.179 --> 00:06:43.380
but after this, the judgment

00:06:43.380 --> 00:06:46.820
and every one of us have a sin issue.

00:06:46.820 --> 00:06:51.820
We are born sinners and sin must be paid for.

00:06:52.079 --> 00:06:56.559
And sin can only be paid for and has been paid for

00:06:56.559 --> 00:07:00.820
with the blood of Jesus Christ over 2000 years ago,

00:07:00.820 --> 00:07:04.940
when he hung upon that cruel cross and he bled and died

00:07:04.940 --> 00:07:07.179
and he was buried and he rose,

00:07:07.179 --> 00:07:09.440
conquering sin, death and the grave.

00:07:09.440 --> 00:07:14.399
He is alive forevermore and he is the savior,

00:07:14.399 --> 00:07:15.700
the only savior.

00:07:15.700 --> 00:07:19.399
And the question this morning is, is he your savior?

00:07:19.399 --> 00:07:22.720
And if you say, yes, he is my savior,

00:07:22.720 --> 00:07:25.720
the people that Paul is writing to, Paul was saved.

00:07:25.720 --> 00:07:29.179
He's writing to the church in Corinth of saved people.

00:07:29.179 --> 00:07:32.040
And he's saying to them, when we live life,

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:36.679
we live desiring God's approval.

00:07:36.679 --> 00:07:39.480
We don't misunderstand this morning,

00:07:39.480 --> 00:07:41.339
Paul's not saying we're gonna live this way

00:07:41.339 --> 00:07:43.359
so that we can earn salvation,

00:07:43.359 --> 00:07:45.119
so that we can get to heaven.

00:07:45.119 --> 00:07:47.859
No, you can't get to heaven by your good works.

00:07:47.859 --> 00:07:49.760
For by grace are you saved through faith

00:07:49.760 --> 00:07:52.299
and that not of yourselves, the gift of God,

00:07:52.299 --> 00:07:55.640
not of works, lest any man should boast.

00:07:55.640 --> 00:07:59.600
The redemption of your soul and of the souls of mankind

00:07:59.600 --> 00:08:01.880
is precious and it was paid for

00:08:01.880 --> 00:08:03.880
with the precious blood of Christ.

00:08:03.880 --> 00:08:06.640
And he offers the gift of eternal life.

00:08:07.399 --> 00:08:08.519
Brother Deal and I and Joseph and Holly,

00:08:08.519 --> 00:08:10.000
we're sitting around the table last night,

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:12.519
talking over dinner, and we're talking about

00:08:12.519 --> 00:08:14.839
some of the visitation opportunities that we had

00:08:14.839 --> 00:08:17.760
and different things that he's been able to experience

00:08:17.760 --> 00:08:20.000
and just recently opportunities.

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:21.880
And one of the things that I mentioned

00:08:21.880 --> 00:08:24.440
is that you try to get people to understand

00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:27.399
that a gift by definition is something

00:08:27.399 --> 00:08:29.040
that someone has paid for.

00:08:30.519 --> 00:08:32.440
You can't earn a gift.

00:08:32.440 --> 00:08:34.280
You can't buy a gift.

00:08:34.320 --> 00:08:38.440
A gift is paid for by someone else.

00:08:38.440 --> 00:08:40.960
And the gift of God, which is eternal life,

00:08:40.960 --> 00:08:44.280
has been paid for by God, the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:08:44.280 --> 00:08:46.559
with his precious blood.

00:08:46.559 --> 00:08:49.880
And so you can't earn it, you can't go forth

00:08:49.880 --> 00:08:51.599
and try to buy it, no.

00:08:51.599 --> 00:08:53.080
It's already been paid for,

00:08:53.080 --> 00:08:56.000
you must simply accept or receive it.

00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:57.320
The Bible says that he came to his own,

00:08:57.320 --> 00:08:59.640
his own received him not, but as many as received him,

00:08:59.640 --> 00:09:02.400
to them gave he power to become the sons of God,

00:09:02.400 --> 00:09:04.599
even to them that believe on his name.

00:09:04.599 --> 00:09:07.599
And so this morning, my salvation,

00:09:07.599 --> 00:09:12.559
my certainty of going to heaven was settled 28 years ago

00:09:12.559 --> 00:09:14.840
when I trust that Christ is my personal savior

00:09:14.840 --> 00:09:17.719
and I am secure in the hand of God.

00:09:17.719 --> 00:09:22.719
The Bible tells us, if you look in John 10 and 1 Peter,

00:09:23.440 --> 00:09:27.880
that we know his voice and we have eternal life

00:09:27.880 --> 00:09:28.799
and we shall never perish.

00:09:28.799 --> 00:09:29.640
Who is that?

00:09:29.640 --> 00:09:30.679
Those that have been saved.

00:09:31.520 --> 00:09:35.799
So when Paul talks about desiring God's approval,

00:09:35.799 --> 00:09:40.239
really I believe what he's talking about is living a life

00:09:40.239 --> 00:09:45.159
in such a way that we're seeking God's smile.

00:09:45.159 --> 00:09:47.039
If I could use that terminology this morning,

00:09:47.039 --> 00:09:50.000
and it reminds me of what Fannie Crosby said,

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:53.520
having that desire as revealed to us in that song,

00:09:53.520 --> 00:09:55.880
my savior, first of all,

00:09:55.880 --> 00:09:58.559
and his smile shall be the first to welcome me.

00:09:58.559 --> 00:09:59.840
You think about that.

00:09:59.840 --> 00:10:04.520
and the desire of living our lives for God's approval.

00:10:04.520 --> 00:10:06.400
So as we look through 2 Corinthians chapter number 10,

00:10:06.400 --> 00:10:08.020
if you're taking notes, notice with me,

00:10:08.020 --> 00:10:10.240
first of all, Paul's approach.

00:10:10.240 --> 00:10:12.540
In verses one through six, the apostle Paul,

00:10:12.540 --> 00:10:15.440
as he begins to answer and to instruct the people

00:10:15.440 --> 00:10:18.980
in Corinth, he's going to reveal to them his approach,

00:10:18.980 --> 00:10:22.000
his approach to life, his approach to ministry,

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:24.800
very particularly, and we find that if we could

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:27.160
summarize his approach in one statement,

00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:29.740
it would be this, to be like Jesus.

00:10:31.040 --> 00:10:33.400
To be like Jesus, and can I tell you this morning,

00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:36.640
as believers, as disciples, followers of the Lord

00:10:36.640 --> 00:10:40.280
Jesus Christ, your approach to life and my desire

00:10:40.280 --> 00:10:43.640
for life should be to be like Jesus.

00:10:43.640 --> 00:10:46.720
They were called Christians first in Antioch, why?

00:10:46.720 --> 00:10:49.080
Because those in Antioch observed their behavior

00:10:49.080 --> 00:10:51.320
and they said they're like Christ,

00:10:51.320 --> 00:10:54.440
and they're called Christians, and they were first

00:10:54.440 --> 00:10:57.020
called disciples, remember Jesus, he calls them

00:10:57.880 --> 00:11:01.180
disciples, and now the word Christian,

00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:03.740
and we carry that term and we use it,

00:11:03.740 --> 00:11:07.020
and we understand this morning that we are to be like Jesus,

00:11:07.020 --> 00:11:09.860
we're to be like Christ, and we find in verse number one,

00:11:09.860 --> 00:11:12.860
notice as Paul begins to approach this, he says,

00:11:12.860 --> 00:11:17.300
now I, Paul, myself, beseech you,

00:11:17.300 --> 00:11:20.020
and then notice what he says, by the meekness

00:11:20.020 --> 00:11:24.660
and gentleness of Christ, who in presence

00:11:24.660 --> 00:11:29.260
am base among you, but being absent and bold towards you.

00:11:29.260 --> 00:11:32.140
So Paul's going to begin to use this terminology

00:11:32.140 --> 00:11:35.020
in verses one and two, that the Judaizers

00:11:35.020 --> 00:11:38.460
were casting these accusations against him,

00:11:38.460 --> 00:11:40.780
and he's going to deal with it in verse two,

00:11:40.780 --> 00:11:42.780
he says, but I beseech you, he uses the word again,

00:11:42.780 --> 00:11:45.500
I beseech you, that I may not be bold

00:11:45.500 --> 00:11:48.100
when I am present with that confidence,

00:11:48.100 --> 00:11:50.820
wherewith I think to be bold against some,

00:11:50.820 --> 00:11:54.180
which think of us as if we walked according

00:11:54.180 --> 00:11:57.460
to the flesh, and so Paul wants to be like Jesus,

00:11:57.460 --> 00:12:01.020
his approach, he mentions in verse number one,

00:12:01.020 --> 00:12:03.740
the meekness and gentleness of Christ,

00:12:03.740 --> 00:12:08.260
I'm thankful for the meekness and gentleness of Christ.

00:12:08.260 --> 00:12:10.860
Jesus Christ has all power, he said,

00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:13.420
all power is given unto me in heaven and in earth,

00:12:13.420 --> 00:12:15.820
but yet he was gentle and he was meek,

00:12:15.820 --> 00:12:18.740
and Paul had authority, we'll get to it

00:12:18.740 --> 00:12:22.520
in just a few moments, but he was using this approach

00:12:22.520 --> 00:12:24.840
to the believers in Corinth that was marked

